<subSubSection id="70B417B5FFC4FFC91687FF37FAAD583A" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3811443EFFC4FFC91687FF37FAAD583A" blockId="28.[151,1437,150,322]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91687FF37FE8059CB" bold="true" box="[199,338,150,176]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC9171EFF36FE2859CB" baseAuthorityName="Merrem" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[350,506,151,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arietans">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC9171EFF36FE2859CB" box="[350,506,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bitis arietans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found throughout sub-Saharan Africa as well as the Arabian Peninsula and 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC4FFC916D7FF1AFF2D59AE" box="[151,255,187,213]" name="Morocco" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, occurring in grassland, open woodland, and scrubland habitats (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC9158FFF1AFB6059AE" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[975,1202,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91279FF1AFBA359AE" box="[1081,1137,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC912FDFF1AFA4359AE" author="Barlow, A. &amp; Wuster, W. &amp; Kelly, C. M. R. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[1213,1425,187,213]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1234 - 1248" refId="ref33576" refString="Barlow, A., Wuster, W., Kelly, C. M. R., Branch, W. R., Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2019) Ancient habitat shifts and organismal diversification are decoupled in the African viper genus Bitis (Serpentes: Viperidae). Journal of Biogeography, 46 (6), 1234 - 1248. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jbi. 13578" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barlow 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC91356FF1AFA9C59AE" box="[1302,1358,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). It is common and widespread in 
<collectingCountry id="40B904AEFFC4FFC91444FF7EFD8B5982" box="[516,601,223,249]" name="Angola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Angola</collectingCountry>
, with the exception of the southwestern desert and some mountain regions (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC916DFFEA2FE595866" author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[159,395,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC9174BFEA2FE945866" box="[267,326,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC917E0FEA2FDCF5867" baseAuthorityName="Merrem" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[416,541,259,284]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arietans">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC917E0FEA2FDCF5867" box="[416,541,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">B. arietans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole representative of the 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC915D4FEA2FC155867" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1842" box="[916,967,259,284]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC915D4FEA2FC155867" box="[916,967,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenera (
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91212FEA2FAFD5866" author="Barlow, A. &amp; Wuster, W. &amp; Kelly, C. M. R. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[1106,1327,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1234 - 1248" refId="ref33576" refString="Barlow, A., Wuster, W., Kelly, C. M. R., Branch, W. R., Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2019) Ancient habitat shifts and organismal diversification are decoupled in the African viper genus Bitis (Serpentes: Viperidae). Journal of Biogeography, 46 (6), 1234 - 1248. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jbi. 13578" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barlow 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC912EFFEA2FB385866" box="[1199,1258,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC91304FEA2FF09583A" author="Ferreira, J. B." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5C3F39CFFFC4FFC916A7FE86FEF25839" author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[231,288,295,322]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">1906</bibRefCitation>
) did not cite this species, although all specimens were identified on the jars as 
<taxonomicName id="FFAE3FBDFFC4FFC912D3FE86FAAA583B" box="[1171,1400,294,321]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Ditera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arietans">
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC912D3FE86FB0E583B" box="[1171,1244,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ditera</emphasis>
[sic] 
<emphasis id="0ADA982CFFC4FFC9135CFE86FAAA583B" box="[1308,1400,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">arietans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
